spec: multiprocessing_extra53
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.Process — Process documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.pool.Pool — Pool documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/process.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra52.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: Process/Queue/Pool/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Value/Array __name__/__module__, Process.__bases__[0].__name__=='BaseProcess', ProcessError/AuthenticationError/BufferTooShort/TimeoutError identity and bases, cpu_count/get_start_method/set_start_method/get_context/active_children __qualname__, exception __module__ and __len__(), context-bound class __qualname__.__len__() tables, Process method __qualname__.__len__() tables, Pool method tables, Process/Pool __mro__.__len__() tables, __all__ metadata, class __dict__.__class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables (extra52), Process/__class__.__name__=='type', cpu_count/__class__.__name__=='method', current_process/__class__.__name__=='function', ProcessError/AuthenticationError/__class__.__name__=='type' (extra45), Process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', current_process/__class__.__module__=='builtins', cpu_count/__class__.__module__=='builtins' (extra46), Pool/__doc__/__class__/__module__=='builtins' (extra50), Pool/__class__.__name__=='type' (multiprocessing_extra). Note: multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext (not a class), so Pool.__class__.__name__ == 'method' and Pool.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper'."
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing.Process.__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') (cross-check for extra46), Pool/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') — Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext, so its __class__ is 'method' from builtins; novel check. Also: active_children/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') and ProcessError/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') and AuthenticationError/__class__.__module__.__eq__('builtins') — not covered by prior extra46 which only covered Process/current_process/cpu_count. Also: Process/__init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function') — Process.__init__ is a plain Python function; no prior multiprocessing spec captured any __init__.__class__ attribute. Note: Pool.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper' (because mp.Pool is a bound method object, not a class), so Pool is excluded from the 'function' init table."
    - "multiprocessing.Pool.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. In the multiprocessing module, Pool is a bound method of the DefaultContext singleton (not a class). The 'method' type is a built-in type defined in the builtins module, so Pool.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' (8 chars). Prior extra46 covered Process/current_process/cpu_count but not Pool. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.active_children.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. active_children is a module-level function; its __class__ is the built-in 'function' type from builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. Prior extra46 covered current_process but not active_children. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. ProcessError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. Prior extra46 did not cover ProcessError. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. AuthenticationError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins'. Prior extra46 did not cover AuthenticationError. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Process is defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py; its __init__ is inherited from BaseProcess and is a plain Python function. The 'function' type has __name__ == 'function'. No prior multiprocessing spec has captured any __init__.__class__ attribute. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "Note: multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext in the multiprocessing module-level namespace (not the Pool class itself from multiprocessing.pool). Therefore Pool.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper', not 'function'. Pool is excluded from the __init__.__class__.__name__=='function' table for accuracy. To access the Pool class directly, use multiprocessing.pool.Pool. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing object __class__.__module__ string equality — extra53
#
# Prior extra46 covered three objects:
#   Process.__class__.__module__         == 'builtins'  (type → builtins)
#   current_process.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'  (function → builtins)
#   cpu_count.__class__.__module__       == 'builtins'  (method → builtins)
#
# Extra53 covers the remaining uncovered objects in the mpmod53 namespace:
#   Pool.__class__.__module__            == 'builtins'  (method → builtins)
#   active_children.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'  (function → builtins)
#   ProcessError.__class__.__module__    == 'builtins'  (type → builtins)
#   AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins'  (type → builtins)
#
# Note: multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method (not a class), so its
# __class__.__name__ == 'method' rather than 'type'.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra53.object_class_module_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing object __class__.__module__ string equality in mpmod53 namespace — Pool/active_children/ProcessError/AuthenticationError not covered by prior extra46; all from builtins"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mpmod53objclsmodule

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Pool,                Pool.__class__.__module__.__eq__,                ["builtins"], true, "Pool.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — mp.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext; 'method' type is from builtins (8 chars); prior extra46 covered Process/current_process/cpu_count but not Pool"]
    - [active_children,     active_children.__class__.__module__.__eq__,     ["builtins"], true, "active_children.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — active_children is a module-level function; its __class__ is the built-in 'function' type from builtins; prior extra46 covered current_process but not active_children"]
    - [ProcessError,        ProcessError.__class__.__module__.__eq__,        ["builtins"], true, "ProcessError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — ProcessError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; prior extra46 did not cover ProcessError"]
    - [AuthenticationError, AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__.__eq__, ["builtins"], true, "AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — AuthenticationError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; prior extra46 did not cover AuthenticationError"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing.Process __init__.__class__.__name__ — extra53
#
# Process.__init__ is a plain Python function defined in Lib/multiprocessing/
# process.py (inherited from BaseProcess). Plain Python functions have
# __class__.__name__ == 'function'. No prior multiprocessing spec has captured
# any __init__.__class__ attribute at all.
#
# Note: multiprocessing.Pool is a bound method object in the module namespace,
# so Pool.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'method-wrapper', not 'function'.
# Pool is therefore excluded from this table.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra53.Process_init_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__init__.__class__.__name__ == 'function' — Process.__init__ is a plain Python function (inherited from BaseProcess) defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py; the 'function' type has __name__ == 'function'; first __init__.__class__.__name__ check in any multiprocessing spec"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["function"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra53
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra53.Pool_class_module_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pool.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — mp.Pool is a bound method of DefaultContext; the 'method' type is a built-in type defined in builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins'; prior extra46 covered Process/current_process/cpu_count but not Pool"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pool.__class__.__module__.__eq__
  args: ["builtins"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra53.active_children_class_module_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.active_children.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — active_children is a module-level function; its __class__ is the built-in 'function' type from builtins; prior extra46 covered current_process but not active_children"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: active_children.__class__.__module__.__eq__
  args: ["builtins"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra53.ProcessError_class_module_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — ProcessError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins' (8 chars); prior extra46 did not cover ProcessError"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ProcessError.__class__.__module__.__eq__
  args: ["builtins"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra53.AuthenticationError_class_module_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__ == 'builtins' — AuthenticationError is a class with metaclass 'type' from builtins; __class__.__module__ == 'builtins'; prior extra46 did not cover AuthenticationError"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: AuthenticationError.__class__.__module__.__eq__
  args: ["builtins"]
  expected: true
